WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:09.313
MAC: Mmm. This stew is really
doing it for me now.

00:09.357 --> 00:11.489
DENNIS:
Well, yeah, 'cause
you're using it as food,

00:11.533 --> 00:13.404
instead of using it
as a reviving mechanism.

00:13.448 --> 00:15.102
Look, there's that truck again.

00:15.145 --> 00:18.366
Oh, goddamn it.
Are you telling me

00:18.409 --> 00:20.107
there's gonna be obnoxious
Americans on this hike?

00:20.150 --> 00:21.804
'Cause that's the last thing
I want to see.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.632
Hey, you guys, wait up a second.

00:23.675 --> 00:25.634
Oh, Frank, why are you carrying
all that stuff, man?

00:25.677 --> 00:27.897
-We're going on a day hike.
-Nah, I just want to make sure

00:27.940 --> 00:31.509
Charlie realizes
I'm still useful, uh, you know,

00:31.553 --> 00:33.772
in case he or Shelley needs
a drink or something to eat.

00:33.816 --> 00:35.948
You got piss in that canteen?

00:35.992 --> 00:38.168
No, I got Gatorade
in that canteen.

00:39.996 --> 00:42.390
The other one's got the piss
in case things go bad.

00:42.433 --> 00:44.827
Oh, there he is.

00:44.870 --> 00:47.090
-[wind whistling]
-Oh.

00:47.134 --> 00:48.222
-MAC: Charlie!
-DENNIS: Hey.

00:48.265 --> 00:50.093
MAC:
Yo, pal.

00:50.137 --> 00:51.877
-Charlie.
-Oh, hello.

00:51.921 --> 00:54.184
I see you all fell for my ruse.

00:54.228 --> 00:55.577
What ruse?
You asking us to go on a hike

00:55.620 --> 00:57.144
with your dad,
and us saying "yes"?

00:57.187 --> 00:58.580
Oldest trick in the book.

00:58.623 --> 01:00.625
Asking someone to do something?

01:00.669 --> 01:01.800
Exactly.

01:01.844 --> 01:03.715
And then, them doing it?

01:03.759 --> 01:05.326
-Precisely, yes.
-FRANK: Wait a minute.

01:05.369 --> 01:07.850
Where-Where's Shelley?
You said he was coming with us.

01:07.893 --> 01:09.373
Oh, yeah.
No, Shelley's coming with us.

01:09.417 --> 01:12.115
He's going on a hike
all the way up the mountain.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.074
Only thing is,
he can't really walk,

01:14.117 --> 01:15.858
so we're gonna have
to carry him.

01:15.901 --> 01:18.252
-Oh.
-What?
-Ugh.

01:18.295 --> 01:21.690
You know, no offense, Charlie,
but Shelley's fat as shit.

01:21.733 --> 01:23.953
Oh, no offense taken, Dennis,
because he is fat as shit,

01:23.996 --> 01:27.739
but, um, he won't really mind us
saying that because he's dead.

01:27.783 --> 01:30.699
What? What the hell
are you talking about?

01:30.742 --> 01:32.918
I'm talking
about Shelley Kelly, my dad.

01:32.962 --> 01:35.007
He's dead.

01:39.882 --> 01:42.537
Oh. Shit.

01:44.495 --> 01:46.280
♪

02:06.343 --> 02:08.693
-This is crazy.
-No, it's not that crazy, Mac.

02:08.737 --> 02:11.348
All right? Look, it's a
Kelly family burial tradition.

02:11.392 --> 02:13.176
We're just gonna carry the man
to the top

02:13.220 --> 02:15.004
of the mountain, and then we're
gonna chuck him over the side.

02:15.047 --> 02:17.049
I-I'm not gonna do that.

02:17.093 --> 02:19.139
Yeah, you know what?
I-I'm not doing it, either.

02:19.182 --> 02:20.705
But not because
I don't think it's awesome.

02:20.749 --> 02:22.142
I think... I think
it's totally awesome.

02:22.185 --> 02:23.926
I just am a little worried
about my back.

02:23.969 --> 02:26.320
-Your back?
-Your back? You've always said

02:26.363 --> 02:27.886
that your back has the symmetry
of the Vitruvian man,

02:27.930 --> 02:29.888
and it's the foundation
of your structural essence.

02:29.932 --> 02:31.977
Yeah, well, why would I want
to ruin my essence, Mac?

02:32.021 --> 02:33.936
I'm not doing it.

02:33.979 --> 02:35.503
Look, guys, the men of my family
have been doing this

02:35.546 --> 02:37.200
for thousands of years,
and it's really important to me

02:37.244 --> 02:39.855
that we keep
this tradition going, okay?

02:39.898 --> 02:43.206
Now I hate to say this, you
know, but it is an emergency.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.513
So I'm just gonna
blurt it right out.

02:45.556 --> 02:47.950
Bros before hoes.

02:47.993 --> 02:49.169
Uh, he's right.
Bros before hoes.

02:49.212 --> 02:50.648
-Yeah, he's got us.
-Oh, my God. Yeah.

02:50.692 --> 02:52.041
Bros before hoes, guys.

02:52.084 --> 02:54.261
That doesn't fit here.
Bros before hoes?

02:54.304 --> 02:55.479
What does that have to do
with anything?

02:55.523 --> 02:57.264
That's sort of
a catch-all, Dee.

02:57.307 --> 02:58.569
Okay, let's just grab a piece

02:58.613 --> 03:00.092
of the bag,
and we'll get it over with.

03:00.136 --> 03:01.093
This is gonna suck,
but let's just...

03:01.137 --> 03:01.964
Bros before hoes.
Bros before...

03:02.007 --> 03:03.357
Bros before hoes. Come on.

03:03.400 --> 03:05.359
-And hoes, too.
-Ugh.

03:05.402 --> 03:07.448
♪

03:19.764 --> 03:21.679
[thunder rumbles]

03:28.338 --> 03:30.384
♪

03:32.995 --> 03:35.519
-Hey.
-Oh, there's got to be
a better way.

03:35.563 --> 03:38.566
Isn't there, like, a sled
or a wagon or something?

03:38.609 --> 03:40.959
No, they didn't slide
my ancestors up the hill.

03:41.003 --> 03:42.831
They didn't wagon them.
They carried them.

03:42.874 --> 03:44.311
Guys, I-I got to be honest.

03:44.354 --> 03:46.617
I'm-I'm getting a little worried
about my back here.

03:46.661 --> 03:48.706
Um, can I suggest something?

03:48.750 --> 03:52.232
What if we burn the body
and carry the ashes up the hill?

03:52.275 --> 03:55.017
-No, no.
-I could consecrate them.

03:55.060 --> 03:57.976
Look, no one is going to torch
or consummate all over my dad.

03:58.020 --> 03:59.674
Yeah, we're here for Charlie.

03:59.717 --> 04:01.371
Charlie, you hungry?
You want a snack?

04:01.415 --> 04:04.331
I got egg, or you want a...?
Want-want some GORP?

04:04.374 --> 04:06.768
-Or how about a...
how about a wine spritzer?
-DEE: Ooh!

04:06.811 --> 04:09.336
-I'll take a spritzer.
-Bros before hoes, Dee.

04:09.379 --> 04:11.860
Frank, can I please have
a white wine spritzer?

04:11.903 --> 04:13.557
-No, no, they're for Charlie.
-DENNIS: Charlie...

04:13.601 --> 04:15.690
Charlie, order me
a wine spritzer, please.

04:15.733 --> 04:17.692
All right, one spritzer
for Mac, please, Frank.

04:17.735 --> 04:19.346
Well, Charlie,
order me one then.

04:19.389 --> 04:20.695
Well, it is bros before hoes,

04:20.738 --> 04:22.218
and not all of the bros
have been spritzed.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.481
-Let's spritz Dennis, Charlie.
-I don't really want one.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.048
Uh, guys,
can I suggest something else?

04:26.091 --> 04:27.963
Uh, what-what if we, uh...?
Now bear with me here.

04:28.006 --> 04:30.139
-What if we chop the body up?
-Come on.

04:30.182 --> 04:33.403
And we carry it in pieces,
right? Or-or melt it somehow.

04:33.447 --> 04:36.537
-Like you did
to Dee's doctor guy?
-Well, what?

04:36.580 --> 04:38.626
-Frank, shut up, man.
-Why? You didn't tell her?

04:38.669 --> 04:41.193
-Tell me what?
-Ha. Well, well,
that doctor showed up

04:41.237 --> 04:42.456
at the castle,
and you weren't there,

04:42.499 --> 04:44.588
so Dennis poured hot oil
on him.

04:44.632 --> 04:45.763
-Charlie, you sure
you don't want to...
-What?!

04:45.807 --> 04:47.765
-[Mac mumbles]
-Shut up! Come on!

04:47.809 --> 04:49.201
-Come on.
-Can we please not drop my dad?

04:49.245 --> 04:50.507
What is he talking about,
Dennis?

04:50.551 --> 04:51.769
Don't worry about it, Dee.
Come on.

04:51.813 --> 04:53.815
It-it wasn't even that hot.

04:53.858 --> 04:55.599
Did you use the murder hole?

04:55.643 --> 04:57.340
Dee, don't get mad at me, okay?

04:57.384 --> 04:58.689
The guy showed up,
and you weren't there.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.561
What was I supposed to do?

05:00.604 --> 05:03.477
-Oh, I don't know.
Not scald him!
-Oh, come on.

05:03.520 --> 05:05.130
You weren't there to enjoy him
so I enjoyed him,

05:05.174 --> 05:07.089
per the castle's wishes.

05:07.132 --> 05:08.699
Are you still talking
to the castle?!

05:08.743 --> 05:10.092
I thought
that was a COVID thing!

05:10.135 --> 05:12.921
-Oh, Dee, let it go. Let it go!
-Uh.

05:12.964 --> 05:16.403
Oh, my God, I cannot
believe this. I am out of here.

05:16.446 --> 05:19.014
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
You can't go.

05:19.057 --> 05:21.059
You-you killed my dad
with your stupid banshee curse.

05:21.103 --> 05:23.061
-My stupid what?
-That's why he died.

05:23.105 --> 05:25.281
Every Kelly saw a banshee
right before he died.

05:25.325 --> 05:27.544
My dad saw you,
so, you got to be here.

05:27.588 --> 05:29.807
-Charlie, banshees aren't real!
-Ow!

05:29.851 --> 05:32.070
-Is that it?
Is that what it was?
-Yes, that could be it.

05:32.114 --> 05:34.856
-Oh, you!
-All right, you know what? Fine.

05:34.899 --> 05:36.858
Go. We don't even need you.
We were probably gonna throw you

05:36.901 --> 05:38.686
-from the top anyway!
-I thought about it.

05:38.729 --> 05:40.514
-Did you think about?
-I did, too. God.

05:40.557 --> 05:42.254
-I was thinking
about it, too, yeah.
-Yeah, well, you got

05:42.298 --> 05:43.778
-to play it safe, you know?
You never know.
-Got to be sure.

05:43.821 --> 05:45.040
-What if she's a witch?
-BOTH: What if she's a witch?

05:49.392 --> 05:53.091
♪

05:53.135 --> 05:55.398
CHARLIE:
Hey, Frank, you okay, there?

05:55.442 --> 05:57.095
-FRANK: I'm ok-- yeah.
-CHARLIE: I got you. Step.

05:57.139 --> 05:58.662
FRANK:
I see it. [groans]

05:58.706 --> 06:00.185
CHARLIE:
There we go.

06:00.229 --> 06:02.405
-The corner here.
-DENNIS: Yeah.

06:02.449 --> 06:04.015
MAC:
I hate to admit it,

06:04.059 --> 06:05.408
but this is a lot heavier
without Dee.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.454
-How much weight
was she bearing?
-I don't know.

06:07.497 --> 06:09.673
Well, it's that monstrous spine
of hers, you know?

06:09.717 --> 06:12.372
The scoliosis hardened it
into petrified wood,

06:12.415 --> 06:14.417
unlike my back which is
pretty much all muscle.

06:14.461 --> 06:16.201
Whoa. Whoa.

06:16.245 --> 06:17.638
-Oh! You all right?
-You-you okay?

06:17.681 --> 06:19.640
Yeah. I'm good. I'm good.

06:19.683 --> 06:21.468
-I just...
-Well, what did...
what did you trip on?

06:21.511 --> 06:24.079
Um, I don't know. Just something
on the ground or something.

06:24.122 --> 06:25.472
Hey, let me jump
back in there, yeah?

06:25.515 --> 06:27.822
Well, w-wait a second.
Did you guys notice

06:27.865 --> 06:30.215
that the body didn't get heavier
when Dennis let go?

06:30.259 --> 06:32.740
No. If anything,
it feels lighter.

06:32.783 --> 06:34.524
Significantly lighter.

06:34.568 --> 06:36.439
That's odd. Uh...

06:36.483 --> 06:39.007
well, I don't know how something
like that could possibly happen.

06:39.050 --> 06:41.313
What-what would explain
something like that? You...

06:41.357 --> 06:43.011
Could it be maybe
the banshee curse? Does it have

06:43.054 --> 06:45.013
-something to do...?
-Were you not carrying it?

06:45.056 --> 06:46.493
Not carr...
What are you talking about, man?

06:46.536 --> 06:48.712
Not carrying it?
Yeah, I was carrying it.

06:48.756 --> 06:50.627
-Why did it get lighter?
-Oh, my God.

06:50.671 --> 06:52.542
It looks like he was
dragging his feet back here.

06:52.586 --> 06:54.936
-Were you hanging on it?
-No!
-He must have

06:54.979 --> 06:56.590
tripped and lost his grip,
and that's how he fell.

06:56.633 --> 06:59.027
-Oh, goddamn it!
-You were taking a ride?

06:59.070 --> 07:01.116
-You weren't even holding it.
-Oh, no. Come on, dude.

07:01.159 --> 07:03.074
Wait. Time out.
Time out, guys.

07:03.118 --> 07:05.076
Can we please not make
dropping my dad a thing? Right?

07:05.120 --> 07:07.035
If you get frustrated,
just place the man down, okay?

07:07.078 --> 07:09.603
I'm sorry. I get frustrated,
I throw. I don't...

07:09.646 --> 07:11.909
All right, listen, listen, guys.
Yes, fine.

07:11.953 --> 07:14.129
Yeah, I was hanging on the bag
a little bit. You know, just

07:14.172 --> 07:16.479
from moment to moment, you know,
just a tiny, tiny bit, okay?

07:16.523 --> 07:19.830
I was trying to decompress
my Vitruvian spine. I'm sorry!

07:19.874 --> 07:22.398
I told you guys it was something
I was worried about.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.835
Guys, we got bigger
problems than this.

07:24.879 --> 07:27.795
How are we gonna get that
up thathill?

07:27.838 --> 07:30.450
-[Mac sighs, whistles]
-CHARLIE: Ugh.

07:30.493 --> 07:31.842
-All right, well...
-DENNIS: Ooh, that's steep.

07:31.886 --> 07:33.844
It's gonna suck, but we'll just
have to carry it.

07:33.888 --> 07:37.326
Okay, well, hold on a second,
Charlie. Let's think about this.

07:37.369 --> 07:40.764
Now, while I do not approve
of Dennis riding your dead dad,

07:40.808 --> 07:42.462
I-I think we have
to think about this

07:42.505 --> 07:44.594
from a...
an engineering perspective.

07:44.638 --> 07:47.597
Now as a Dutch man,
I think I would

07:47.641 --> 07:51.035
look at this the way I would
think of a windmill or a dam.

07:51.079 --> 07:53.211
Cool. How's a windmill
gonna help us?

07:53.255 --> 07:56.737
I haven't been Dutch long enough
to know.

07:56.780 --> 07:58.303
Well, if we had
a really giant windmill,

07:58.347 --> 07:59.783
we could just
blow him up the hill.

07:59.827 --> 08:01.089
-We could blow him up the hill.
-Oh, giant windmill

08:01.132 --> 08:02.525
-could blow him up. Good.
-Oh, yeah. Huh.

08:02.569 --> 08:03.526
Do you have your giant windmill
in your bag?

08:03.570 --> 08:04.875
Hold on a second. Let...

08:04.919 --> 08:06.137
Let me suggest something else.

08:06.181 --> 08:07.791
Uh, what if we, uh...

08:07.835 --> 08:09.750
what if we slide him up
the steep part of the hill?

08:09.793 --> 08:10.968
-Uh...
-Yeah, wait, wait, wait, wait.

08:11.012 --> 08:12.883
Frank, do you have a tent
in that bag?

08:12.927 --> 08:15.146
Yeah I got a tent.
I got a tent.

08:15.190 --> 08:18.236
-Oh, how's that for
being resourceful, Charlie?
-Oh, okay.

08:18.280 --> 08:19.934
-Okay, okay.
-Now, well, look,
this-this is good!

08:19.977 --> 08:22.153
Now-now, Charlie,
we're still honoring your dad.

08:22.197 --> 08:25.156
-Right.
-We're just sliding him
up this one section. That's it!

08:25.200 --> 08:27.245
[sighs]
All right, fine.

08:27.289 --> 08:28.943
We'll slide the man up the hill,
just this part.

08:28.986 --> 08:30.205
But then, we'll go back
to carrying him!

08:30.248 --> 08:32.903
All of us, please.

08:33.948 --> 08:36.690
-Yeah.
-All right.

08:36.733 --> 08:38.430
-Pop the tent out. Let's get it.
Let's get it.
-Dude, help me

08:38.474 --> 08:40.041
-with this thing.
You got to... you got to...
-I got it.

08:40.084 --> 08:41.738
-Keep it on. I'll just
get it out of here.
-Okay.

08:41.782 --> 08:44.045
ALL:
One, two, three. [grunting]

08:44.088 --> 08:47.396
ALL:
One, two, three.
[grunting]

08:47.439 --> 08:50.704
One, two, three.
[grunting]

08:50.747 --> 08:53.228
[all panting]

08:53.271 --> 08:55.273
-One, two, three.
-Two, three.

08:55.317 --> 08:58.015
[all grunting, muttering]

08:58.059 --> 08:59.843
-And now, yes!
-Oh!

08:59.887 --> 09:02.367
-All right, all right, boys.
-Ah, that worked out good!

09:02.411 --> 09:03.934
-[Frank chuckles]
-[Dennis and Mac whoop]
-I got to say, too,

09:03.978 --> 09:06.284
-that still felt respectful.
-That wasn't so bad.
-Ah.

09:06.328 --> 09:07.895
Guys, I actually feel like

09:07.938 --> 09:09.810
that was a back-strengthening
exercise for me.

09:09.853 --> 09:11.551
-Awesome!
-All right, good.

09:11.594 --> 09:13.248
-Let's just take a rest
here, all right?
-Yeah.

09:13.291 --> 09:15.337
-Okay. Want a GORP?
Anybody into GORP?
-ALL: Yeah.

09:15.380 --> 09:16.686
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Let me get it out.
Let me get it out.

09:16.730 --> 09:18.470
-Let's get some GORP.
-All right, get it out.

09:18.514 --> 09:20.037
-Maybe, guys, let's have
a couple of spritzers.
-Spritzers!

09:20.081 --> 09:21.256
Who wants one? Spritzer for Mac,
spritzer for Dennis.

09:21.299 --> 09:22.605
I-I got spritzers,
yeah, I got spritzers.

09:22.649 --> 09:23.954
Then we'll get this
old bitch up the hill.

09:23.998 --> 09:25.869
-All right. Oh.
-Ah, this is gonna be good.

09:25.913 --> 09:28.568
-Oh!
-Oh, shit!
-Oh, my God.

09:28.611 --> 09:30.265
ALL:
Whoa.

09:30.308 --> 09:32.093
-FRANK: Oh.
-[body thudding]

09:37.925 --> 09:41.581
Oh. Oh.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.495
-Okay, that's my bad.
-Oh.

09:43.539 --> 09:45.280
Okay. That is, uh...

09:45.323 --> 09:47.412
That's gonna be a mess
inside that bag, guys.

09:47.456 --> 09:49.893
Oh, yeah. That's one big sack
of Irish stew.

09:49.937 --> 09:53.549
-Phew.
-Yeah, yeah. Okay, all right.

09:53.593 --> 09:55.377
Okay, that-that... This isn't
a problem. All right, I...

09:55.420 --> 09:57.640
What do you say
we go back down there,

09:57.684 --> 10:01.383
and we dump out whatever liquid
is probably in that body bag,

10:01.426 --> 10:03.385
and then, that'll-that'll
lighten the load?

10:03.428 --> 10:05.866
-Okay, yeah.
That works for me, yeah.
-Okay.

10:05.909 --> 10:07.302
And-and then we can carry it up,
no problem!

10:07.345 --> 10:08.999
-Yeah, yeah.
-All right.

10:09.043 --> 10:12.263
I'm starting to see myself as
more of a problem solver. I...

10:12.307 --> 10:13.917
I-I think that actually could be
a new identity.

10:13.961 --> 10:15.440
I'm gonna put that
on the list.

10:15.484 --> 10:16.833
You guys are gonna want
to hear this.

10:16.877 --> 10:19.053
So, uh, uh, Dutch first.

10:19.096 --> 10:21.882
Dutch first, then gay,
then problem solver.

10:21.925 --> 10:23.231
Now could you repeat that back
to me? 'Cause I think...

10:23.274 --> 10:24.754
Oh, dude, shut up! Oh, my God!

10:24.798 --> 10:26.277
All right, you're Irish, Mac.

10:26.321 --> 10:29.498
-Yeah. You're not Dutch.
-What?

10:29.541 --> 10:31.239
You're Irish. Right,
but we knew you were gonna be

10:31.282 --> 10:33.328
so goddamn annoying about it
on the trip,

10:33.371 --> 10:35.069
and that it was gonna be
the only thing you talked about,

10:35.112 --> 10:36.766
so we paid your mom to tell you
you were Dutch.

10:36.810 --> 10:38.420
It cost us a couple of loosies.

10:38.463 --> 10:40.291
-Yeah.
-Yeah, your mom does not
like you, dude.

10:40.335 --> 10:42.337
Yeah, but, I mean,
Luther Vandross? Mac, really?

10:42.380 --> 10:44.382
-Luther Vandross?
-[laughs] Come on, Mac.

10:44.426 --> 10:46.167
But somehow it's been
even worse! You're talking

10:46.210 --> 10:48.909
about your identity even more.
I can't believe it.

10:48.952 --> 10:50.824
Why would you do that?

10:50.867 --> 10:52.260
And by the way-- the tattoo?
The... Can we talk about that--

